📚 Subject: Computer Organization & Architecture (COA)
🧠 Topic: Basic Computer Organization & Instruction Set

1️⃣ Concept Teaching (Strict, Clear, GATE-Oriented)
🔹 What is Computer Organization?

Computer Organization deals with:

👉 How hardware components are connected
👉 How instructions are executed

🔹 Basic Components of Computer
1️⃣ CPU (Central Processing Unit)
Brain of computer
Executes instructions
2️⃣ ALU (Arithmetic Logic Unit)
Performs arithmetic & logical operations
3️⃣ Control Unit (CU)
Controls execution
Sends control signals
4️⃣ Registers
Small, fast memory inside CPU
5️⃣ Memory
Stores data and instructions
🔹 Instruction Cycle (VERY IMPORTANT)

Steps:

1️⃣ Fetch
2️⃣ Decode
3️⃣ Execute

Explanation:
Fetch → Get instruction from memory
Decode → Understand instruction
Execute → Perform operation

📌 GATE frequently asks order.

